<h2 id="technology-and-framework-used">Technology and Framework used</h2>
<hr />

<ul>
  <li>React Native Framework</li>
  <li>Java, JavaScript, Objective-C and GitHub CLI</li>
  <li>NPM, NPM Scripts, Nativebase, Android Native Library</li>
</ul>

<h2 id="code-example">Code Example</h2>
<hr />

<p>In <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">src/abstract files</code>, you can add your any dependencies there needed by your application. In short, we can illustrate it in simple graph:</p>

<p><img width="400" height="300" src="https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/38276345/102958422-c4029500-4517-11eb-81e3-cbb9b0f668c4.png" /></p>

<p>And we can then express them in code:</p>
<div class="language-javascript highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code><span class="c1">// Dependencies</span>
<span class="k">export</span> <span class="k">default</span> <span class="kd">class</span> <span class="nx">Dependency</span> <span class="kd">extends</span> <span class="nx">React</span><span class="p">.</span><span class="nx">Components</span> <span class="p">{</span>
    <span class="nx">onSubmit</span><span class="p">()</span> <span class="p">{</span>
        <span class="nx">console</span><span class="p">.</span><span class="nx">log</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="dl">"</span><span class="s2">Success!</span><span class="dl">"</span><span class="p">);</span>
    <span class="p">}</span>
<span class="p">}</span>
</code></pre></div></div>
<div class="language-javascript highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code><span class="c1">// Abstract</span>
<span class="k">export</span> <span class="p">{</span> <span class="k">default</span> <span class="k">as</span> <span class="nx">Dependency</span> <span class="p">}</span> <span class="k">from</span> <span class="dl">'</span><span class="s1">./helper/method/dependency</span><span class="dl">'</span><span class="p">;</span>

<span class="c1">// Or you can also write it like this to avoid bugs:</span>

<span class="k">import</span> <span class="nx">Dependency</span> <span class="k">from</span> <span class="dl">'</span><span class="s1">./helper/method/dependecy</span><span class="dl">'</span><span class="p">;</span>
<span class="k">export</span> <span class="p">{</span> <span class="nx">Dependency</span> <span class="p">};</span>
</code></pre></div></div>
<p>Learn more at <a href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/web/javascript/reference/statements/export">MDN Mozilla Export Guideline</a></p>

<div class="language-javascript highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code><span class="c1">// Component</span>
<span class="k">import</span> <span class="o">*</span> <span class="k">as</span> <span class="nx">Abstract</span> <span class="k">from</span> <span class="dl">'</span><span class="s1">./src/abstract</span><span class="dl">'</span><span class="p">;</span>

<span class="k">export</span> <span class="k">default</span> <span class="kd">class</span> <span class="nx">Dependecies</span> <span class="kd">extends</span> <span class="nx">React</span><span class="p">.</span><span class="nx">Components</span> <span class="p">{</span>
    <span class="nx">Abstract</span><span class="p">.</span><span class="nx">onSubmit</span><span class="p">()</span> <span class="c1">// Output "Success!"</span>
<span class="p">}</span>
</code></pre></div></div>

<h2 id="installation">Installation</h2>
<hr />

<ol>
  <li>git clone https://github.com/workpebojot/Vacuum.git</li>
  <li>cd Vacuum</li>
  <li>git init</li>
  <li>npm install</li>
</ol>

<h2 id="how-to-use">How to use</h2>
<hr />

<p>In order to use this app, you have two options, you can use either use AVD or ADB support. To setup AVD, you can head to AVD Manual Guide at Android Developer Website: <a href="https://developer.android.com/studio/run/managing-avds.html">Create New AVD</a>. To setup ADB, plug in your devices and run <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">react-native run-android</code>. However, since this app is still new, Iâ€™m not still sure if <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">react-native run-ios</code> will run correctly. But it will sure it can be configured for right patching.</p>

